Year = {{2019}},
Volume = {{17}},
Month = {{MAR 28}},
Abstract = {{Background: Coproduction, a collaborative model of research that
   includes stakeholders in the research process, has been widely advocated
   as a means of facilitating research use and impact. We summarise the
   arguments in favour of coproduction, the different approaches to
   establishing coproductive work and their costs, and offer some advice as
   to when and how to consider coproduction.
