Abstract = {{The most important impacts of social movements are often cultural, but
   the sheer variety of potential cultural impacts-from shifts in public
   opinion to new portrayals of a group on television to the metrics
   guiding funding in a federal agency-presents unique challenges to
   scholars. Rather than treating culture as a social sphere separate from
   politics and the economy, we conceptualize it as the ideas, values, and
   assumptions underpinning policies and practices in all spheres. We
   review recent research on movements' impacts on public opinion and
   everyday behavior; the media and popular culture; nonpolitical
