Abstract = {{The concept of resilience is used by many in different ways: as a
   scientific concept, as a guiding principle, as inspirational `buzzword',
   or as a means to become more sustainable. Next to the academic debate on
   meaning and notions of resilience, the concept has been widely adopted
   and interpreted in policy contexts, particularly related to climate
   change and extreme weather events. In addition to having a positive
   connotation, resilience may cover aspects that are missed in common
   disaster risk Management approaches. Although the precise definition of
   resilience may remain subject of discussion, the views on what is
   important to consider in the management of extreme weather events do not
   differ significantly. Therefore, this paper identifies the key
