Abstract = {{Understanding the relationship between human well-being and the stress
   economic activity places on the environment is a central challenge of
   sustainability research. Lamb et al (2014 Environ. Res. Lett. 9 014011)
   provide two important results that will influence future analyses.
   First, they show that the drivers of consumption that induce
   anthropogenic carbon emissions are similar to but not the same as the
   drivers of place-based (i.e., production driven) carbon emissions.
