   of known or suspected thresholds that can lead to irreversible (or
   practically irreversible) changes in the productivity and value of
   assets and hence social welfare. These thresholds allow us to identify
   policies or projects that may be leading to an increased risk of decline
   in capital stocks (the wealth of the region). Such risks are not
   reflected through usualmeasures of current system performance, e. g.
